Annotation.note:
The point $H$, $O$ are the orthocenter and the circumcenter of the triangle
$ABC$ and $P$, $Q$ are two points symmetrical with respect to the mediator
of $BC$. The perpendicular from $P$ to $BC$ meets $BC$ in $R$ and $OQ$ in
$S$. $M$ is the midpoint of $HP$. Prove that (a) $MR$ is parallel to $AS$;
(b) $2*MR=AS$; (c) the symmetric of $R$ with respect to the midpoint of
$OM$ lies on $AQ$.

\begin{keywords}
geometry theorem proving
\end{keywords}
